Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for subjective evaluation tasks in the context of an online coaching platform, which involves elements of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also explores the use of machine learning algorithms for the same task, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) and computational social science (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of eliciting useful insights from crowdsourced data, which is a topic of interest in the field of social informatics (cs.SI).
